    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities drifted slightly lower today, with the S&P 500 and NASDAQ each shedding 0.1% in a low-conviction session as investors balanced resilient corporate earnings against lingering uncertainty over trade policy and Federal Reserve rate expectations. The muted action reflected a market in consolidation mode \u2014 buyers and sellers roughly in equilibrium \u2014 with no major catalyst to break the recent range. Small- and mid-cap momentum names outperformed large-caps, suggesting selective risk appetite persists beneath the flat headline numbers.",
